Bring a #small pot{} of water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} into strips. Drain and rinse
@black beans{13.4%oz can}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim and discard root
end from @baby lettuce{1}; chop into bite-size pieces until you have about 4
loose cups (8 loose cups for 4 servings). Dice @roma tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces.

Once water is boiling, using a #spoon{}, carefully lower @eggs{2} into #pot.
Reduce heat to low and cover #pot. Simmer until hard boiled, ~{11%minutes}
(you'll finish the eggs in step 5).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add poblano and beans; season with @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until poblano is browned
and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Let cool at least ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @sour cream{4%tbsp},
@buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%oz}, @sugar{1%tsp}, a pinch of lime zest, juice
from two lime wedges, and @chipotle powder{1/4%tsp} (taste and add more if you
like things spicy). Season lightly with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Once eggs have cooked 11 minutes, drain, keeping eggs in #pot. Cover eggs with
enough cold water to cover by 2 inches. Soak until cool to the touch,
~{5-10%minutes}.

Peel eggs. Quarter eggs lengthwise; season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Rinse peeled eggs with water to remove shell fragments.

In a #large bowl{}, toss lettuce, tomato, and bean mixture with half the dressing.

Divide salad between plates. Top with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup},
eggs, remaining dressing, and remaining lime zest. Crumble @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz}
over top. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.